  {newline}
  Warrior Priest of Sigmar{newline}
  - Gains access to buffs and some damaging abilities {newline}
  - Melee fighter with powerful survival skills{newline}
  - Bonuses to all Simgarite units{newline}
  {newline}
  {newline}
  Bretonnia: {newline}
  {newline}
  Knight of Bretonnia{newline}
  - Focus on mounted combat and charging into the fray{newline}
  - Holy and physical damage types{newline}
  - Bonuses for horses and knight units{newline}
  {newline}
  Damsel of the Lady{newline}
  - Gains access to both spells and prayers{newline}
  - Bonuses and buffs for Bretonnian troops {newline}
  - Unlocks three schools of magic{newline}
  {newline}
  {newline}
  Vampire Counts:{newline}
  {newline}
  Vampire Nobility{newline}
  - The ability to fly during battle via the Mistform ability{newline}
  - Gains access to Necromancy{newline}
  - Can learn two lores of magic{newline}
  {newline}
  Blood Knight{newline}
  - No access to magic but very powerful in melee, with a large health pool{newline}
  - Gains the ability to convert worthy opponents into Blood Knight units{newline}
  - Armour penetrating attacks in the late game{newline}
