  {newline}

To use magic in battle you simply have to, assuming the magic path was chosen, press Q (which can be remapped at your convenience). This will make your character enter spellcasting mode, providing you with an aiming reticule or an AoE outline, depending on the spell type. The player can scroll through his available spells by using the mouse wheel. The one you have selected at any given time is displayed at the bottom left of your screen.{newline} 
  {newline}We have also implemented our own ‘quick-cast’ system, which by default is the middle mouse button, and skips the aiming process when desired. What you can cast, as well as how often you can cast, is entirely dependent on your Winds of Magic resource (mana) and the individual cooldown of each spell. {newline}
  {newline}Winds of Magic
  {newline}All spells cost winds of Magic to cast. Winds of Magic are recharged by letting time pass on the campaign map. The current amount of Winds of Magic can be found in the lower right corner on the campaign map, and in the left corner during battles. In battle, this resource is depleted for every spell you cast.{newline}
  {newline}Lores of Magic
  {newline}The Old Realms currently features the following lores of magic:{newline}
  - Fire {newline}
  - Light {newline}
  - Dark {newline}
  - Necromancy {newline}
  - Heavens {newline}
  - Life {newline}
  - Beasts {newline}
 {newline}Players will have access to all of these, however, there are restrictions. Not every character can master multiple lores. Some Vampires can for example master Dark magic and Necromancy, whereas Damsels can master up to 3 lores. Based on certain {TOR_CAREERS}, races and the faction you join, the potential school selection and amount varies.  
 {newline}
 {newline}Each of these lores has its own progression with a range of unique spells, all of which are tied to our custom-made Spellcraft skill. Adding points in the Spellcraft skill raises your Winds of Magic capacity as well as its regeneration rate on the campaign map.{newline}
 {newline}
 {newline}

Spell Book can be accessed via the character screen and it stores all knowledge of magic, this includes companions in your party. In your spell book you can find information on the character's magic abilities such as their maximum Winds of Magic or mastered spells.{newline}
  {newline}All known and learnable spells are listed under their appropriate lore inside the spell book, which can be selected via the bookmark on the left side.{newline}
  {newline}Spell descriptions can be read by hovering the mouse cursor over the spells.

Certain characters and factions are able to raise the dead or offer characters the ability to become undead. The player can access this feature by playing as a necromancer or a Vampire. {newline}
  {newline}Post Battle Resurrection
  {newline}Based on your Discipline level (see {TOR_ATTRIBUTES}) there is a chance that every living creature that died in a battle will become a lesser undead warrior and join your army.{newline}
  {newline}Raiding Tombs
  {newline}As a necromancer you can also try your luck to resurrect undead in local graveyards, found as a new option within villages. Of course this has some risk, as most of the ‘good’ factions will immediately dislike you, furthermore if you choose to try and raise undead in towns or villages, you may be caught by the locals and will have to fight to survive. {newline}
  {newline}Priests and other careers are unable to perform Necromancy.
  {newline}

Discipline is an attribute made specifically for TOR and it contains three new core skills.{newline}
  {newline}Gunpowder
  {newline}The Gunpowder skill accounts for weapons like pistols, handguns or even grenade-launching blunderbusses. To level up this skill, use gunpowder weapons or read Skill Books (see {TOR_SKILLBOOKS}) to obtain the minimal requirement for most guns. Characters and gunpowder units in the party will benefit from several perks and benefits directed to this new weapon type. Note that artillery pieces like Cannons are governed by the Engineering skill, not Gunpowder.{newline}
  {newline}Spellcraft
  {newline}The Spellcraft skill is exclusive to all characters able to perform magic. Several perks will increase the character's magic capabilities or his use of arcane knowledge. Skills are obtained via fighting with - and using magic in combat. New spells can be learned from Magister NPCs.{newline}
  {newline}Faith
  {newline}The Faith skill is exclusive to all believing peoples of the Old World - Necromancers and Vampires cannot level this skill. Faith can be increased by praying at a shrine (see {TOR_RELIGION}) or in the case of some specific careers, by performing prayers during battles. Faith increases the duration of blessings obtained from shrines. {newline}
  {newline}
  {newline}

Regiments of Renown (RoR) are unique factional troops that can only be recruited from specific locations and settlements on the campaign map, marked with a ‘RoR’ icon. Once you enter the settlement marked with ‘RoR’, there will be an option to select on the settlement menu.{newline}
  {newline}Those units cannot be recruited at the start. Instead, you must be a part of the appropriate faction and/or have reached a certain level of renown. Until these requirements have been met you will be refused recruitment of any Regiments of Renown.
  {newline}
  {newline}

Around the world, players can find several locations where characters can receive blessings of various gods. Those blessings provide buffs for the whole party. Praying at a shrine can attract religious units like Flagellants or Battle Plgrims, which join the praying party. Note that the player as well as other lords can benefit from praying at a shrine. Additionally, your devotion for a god rises whenever you pray at a shrine.{newline}
  {newline}In the current update 3 religions are implemented and each provide their own unique blessings. {newline}
  {newline}Taal, the All-father of the human gods, patron of hunters, provides a movement buff when the party is travelling through forest terrain.{newline}
  {newline}Sigmar, the Uniter of mankind, provides a health regeneration buff for heroes in the party.{newline}
  {newline}The Lady of the Lake, the chief goddess of Bretonnia, provides a morale buff for all units within a party.{newline}
  {newline}Praying at a shrine is related to the Faith skill and higher Faith skill will prolong the blessing effect.
  {newline}New features can also be unlocked, like “donations” which allow the player to increase renown by donating items to a shrine.{newline}
  {newline}
  {newline}
  {newline}

Skill books are another feature we have implmented alongside the Magister NPCs. Th Magisters will sell them and very similarily to Mount and Blade: Warband, you will passively read the book as you travel or rest. Skill Books grant skill experience when they are being read. Books are sold for a fair amount so they aren’t easily accessed from the start of the game. To read a book you must have it inside your inventory.
  {newline}
  {newline}Click on the book to reveal its description and a magnifying glass icon will appear in the lower right corner. If you have not already read that book, you will see a text notification stating that a book was selected for reading. If you already read that book, it will state that you are already familiar with this book. When time passes (by travelling or resting) you will read the contents of the book and your appropriate skill will increase. No book can be read twice.{newline}
  {newline}
  {newline}

To start the game as a Vampire, you must choose the ‘Vampire nobility’ option during character creation. When you load onto the campaign map your character will have the appearance and powers of a Vampire, such as access to magic, Necromancy and other abilities planned for the future.{newline}
  {newline}If you wish to become a Vampire after starting the game as a regular human, join the Vampire Counts and speak to Mannfred Von Carstein once you have sufficient renown and relations. Alternatively, you have to be part of the Order of the Blood Dragon, and ask Walach Harkon to become a Blood Knight. Doing so will provide an option to ‘receive the Blood Kiss’ which will then change your character into a Vampire and replace your career with the Blood Knight or Vampire Noble.
  {newline}
  {newline}Vampires learn new magic through Dark Magister NPCs found in settlements, similar to standard magic users.{newline}
  {newline}
  {newline}

Priest Careers and Prayers
  {newline}Starting as the Priest Acolyte, or the Damsel of the Lady, will make the player representative of the beliefs in the Old World. They are the only careers and peoples that have access to prayers or battle prayers.{newline}
  {newline}Other than spells, prayers are directly unlocked upon reaching a certain skill level of the Faith skill. Starting with the adept skill at the “Novice Prayer” prayer perk up to the “Grand prayer” perk at skill 125, new prayers will be unlocked. Non Priest career types, cannot unlock any prayers for combat but can receive the blessings from {TOR_RELIGION}. {newline}
  {newline}Prayers have no cost and can be quite powerful. To make these abilities balanced, the cooldown is shared across all prayers and it is fairly long. Addionally prayers are not available to cast at the battle start. Naturally, Vampires and necromancers don't get access to prayers.{newline}
  {newline}In the current update the following prayers are available:{newline}
  {newline}Sigmar
  {newline}- Healing Hand: Troops inside the area get healed for 5 health points per second for a total duration of 9 seconds.
  {newline}- Armour of the Righteous: Allies in a 3 meter radius gain 35% physical resistance for 8 seconds.
  {newline}- Vanquish: Allies in a target radius gain the burning weapon trait that ignites enemies and deals fire damage.
  {newline}- Comet of Sigmar: A projectile is launched at the enemy, dealing about 30 holy damage. The explosion can knock down enemies and dismount riders.{newline}
  {newline}
  {newline}Lady of the Lake
  {newline}- Aura of the Lady: Provides 80% reduction from magic, fire and lightning to allies in the area.
  {newline}- Shield Of Combat: Adds 40% physical resistance against ranged damage for 15 seconds to the caster and surrounding friendly units.
  {newline}- Lady's Favour: Increases attack speed of allied units inside the area by 25%.
  {newline}- Aerial Shield: Completely protects allies inside the area from ranged damage.
  {newline}
  {newline}
  {newline}

From time to time while travelling through the world, events can occur that need the action of the player. During those events, the game can’t be saved and the story has to be finished before the game continues. {newline}
{newline}
Based on character skills and other attributes, like being a Necromancer or Vampire, the choices and approaches in the situation differ, and the chance of a positive outcome varies. The outcome of those events can affect the world.{newline}
{newline}
These events are triggered randomly and are sometimes based on situations and the surroundings of the player. {newline}
{newline}
{newline}

The Old World is a home to many extraordinary creatures, some of which can also act as powerful mounts.
  {newline}As of now, our mod features only three such creatures: the majestic Demigryphs of the Empire, Zombie Horses and spectral Ghost Horses of the Vampire Counts.{newline}
  {newline}At this point Zombie and Ghost Horses can be bought from traders and Demigryphs can only be acquired as rare battle loot. There are plans to implement specific quests which would award the player with these mounts.{newline}
  {newline}
  {newline}
